## Task 3 Rules in Firewalls

Objective: Learn how firewall rules control traffic.
Rule Components:
- Source Address
- Destination Address
- Port
- Protocol
- Action (Allow, Deny, Forward)
- Direction (Inbound, Outbound, Forward)
Examples:
- Allow outbound HTTP (port 80).
- Deny inbound SSH (port 22).
- Forward inbound HTTP to web server.
- Outcome: Rules provide granular control over traffic flow.

