## Task 4 Windows Defender Firewall

Objective: Configure Windows Defender Firewall.
- Built-in firewall in Windows OS.
- Profiles: Private (home/trusted) and Public (untrusted).
Options: allow/disallow apps, block all incoming connections, restore defaults.
Custom Rule Example:
- Block outbound HTTP/HTTPS (ports 80,443).
- Steps: Advanced Settings → Outbound Rules → New Rule → TCP → Specific Ports → Block → Apply to all profiles → Name rule.
- Outcome: Browsing websites fails, confirming rule works.
- Exercise: Review created rules to identify blocked traffic.

