## Task 5 Linux iptables Firewall

Objective: Explore Linux firewall utilities.
Netfilter Framework: Provides packet filtering, NAT, and connection tracking.
Utilities:
- iptables: Widely used, flexible.
- nftables: Successor to iptables, more efficient.
- firewalld: Zone-based, predefined rule sets.
ufw (Uncomplicated Firewall): Beginner-friendly wrapper for iptables.
ufw Commands:
- Check status: sudo ufw status
- Enable firewall: sudo ufw enable
- Allow all outgoing traffic: sudo ufw default allow outgoing
- Deny incoming SSH: sudo ufw deny 22/tcp
- List rules: sudo ufw status numbered
- Delete rule: sudo ufw delete <rule_number>
- Outcome: Linux users can manage traffic with different utilities depending on expertise.

