## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Keep firewalls enabled by default.
- Apply least privilege: deny by default, allow only necessary traffic.
- Regularly audit firewall rules.
- Monitor logs for anomalies.
- Choose Linux firewall utility based on skill level.

## Conclusion

- Firewalls are critical for both Windows and Linux environments.
- Windows Defender Firewall offers accessible GUI-based management.
- Linux provides powerful command-line utilities.
- Proper configuration ensures strong defense against unauthorized traffic.
